remarks: A nonempty, bounded-above set of reals has a supremum.  Axiom 22 of 22 for real and complex numbers, derived from ZF set theory.  Note:  The more general version with ordering on extended reals is ~ axsup .  This construction-dependent theorem should not be referenced directly; instead, use ~ ax-pre-sup .  (Contributed by NM, 19-May-1996.)  (Revised by Mario Carneiro, 16-Jun-2013.)  (New usage is discouraged.)
